Government of Maharashtra

Lokmanya Tilak Marg, Mantralaya, Mumbai - Yoo 0019

Read: -

1) The Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal vide the Administrative Sanction Order No. Z. No. / YJP / Grapapuvi / Jipavaswami / 4040/2022 D. 29.07.2022 2) Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal Original Technical Approval Order No. 850/123 Kaapapu / Yajip / Tansha / Jajimi / 2022-23, d. 14.07.2022 3) Revised Technical Accreditation Order No.1 of the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal. 1867/268 Kaapapu / Yajip / Tansha / Jajimi / 2023-24, d. 03.01.2025 4) Letter from CEO, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal No. 07.01.2025
The Proposal: -

Yavatmal district. Saidabad Ta. ATI (Scheme Code - 20032288) The original budget of the tap water supply scheme was prepared by the CEO, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal vide Reference No. Technical approval is provided under Section 2. Also, Reference No. 1 under Rs. 29,40,500 - Such a modest price has been granted administrative approval. The Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal has also proposed to give revised administrative approval to the proposed tap water supply scheme vide Reference Letter No. 4 here. The VATS of 07.01.2025 has been submitted to the government. Reference No. 3 here.

Under the letter dated 03.01.2025, the government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price as per the revised technical approval given by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal.
The Government's Decisions:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Md. Saidabad Ta. The scheme of tap water supply scheme is being given revised administrative approval at a price of Rs. 30,82,200 / - (Rupees Three Lakh Eighty Two Hundred Only) subject to the following conditions as the cost of the scheme has increased on account of increase in Goods and Services Tax (GST) rates.
Government Decision No: Supra 2025 / Q. 31 / AT 2 (E Office No.1071977)
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval as well as the original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred every year for implementation, maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), reduction in the scheme or renovation of machinery.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) A CAG report in 2013 shows that 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity bills. In fact, in order to make the scheme financially viable, it will be the responsibility of the concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad to increase the water tariff as per the requirement.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
9) Since no administrative expenditure is admissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.

2. Schemes for which tenders have been floated. The increased cost of revised cost of the scheme, which has already been approved, should be met from the sanctioned grant of Jal Jeevan Mission programme only.
as well as the plans. The Discovered / Approved Cost concept is applicable to schemes with 21.06.2022 and subsequent work orders. Discovered / Approved Costs for Paid Plans
2 out of 4
Government Decision No: Supra 2025 / Q. 31 / AT 2 (E Office No.1071977)

The expenditure up to the limit should be met from the approved Central and State share grants as per the guidelines issued from time to time of the Jal Jeevan Mission programme. Also, as per the revised WISH norms, the remaining cost from the sanctioned cost to the discovered / approved cost should be met from the sanctioned grant of Jal Jeevan Mission programme only.
3. The revised administrative approval is the technicalities of the proposal received from the Regional Offices.

Government approval should not be taken into account in case of tender proceedings and territorial decisions or irregularities. Therefore, if such a case arises, the relevant enforcement mechanism will be solely responsible for it.

4. Revised administrative approval to the proposed scheme is provided by the Department of Finance. No. 2013 / Q. No. 30/2013 Regulations, Part-II Part I of this Government Decision, No. (six) Paragraph No. 27 (a) is being granted in accordance with the authority conferred on the Department.
5. Shifting of connection is not permitted under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme" and should not be implemented if this provision is made in the revised scheme.
The Government decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
